{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845023224,"sessionID":"ses_28765cb2bffeNQmeQ6uKmEUucF","part":{"id":"prt_d789ae2f500115MXzNj0KMc7Jy","messageID":"msg_d789aceb2001WUGRJRjw6kCOiJ","sessionID":"ses_28765cb2bffeNQmeQ6uKmEUucF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_76900e9284394d11991e69f7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-007\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe K8s Reconciler Controller is a Kubernetes controller that watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources and ensures the desired runtime state matches the actual cluster state. It provides declarative management of sandbox runtimes through the Kubernetes API server, enabling native Kubernetes patterns for resource lifecycle management.\n\n### 1.2 Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── controller/\n│   ├── controller.go           # Controller framework & reconciliation loop\n│   ├── reconciler.go           # Reconciler implementation\n│   ├── agentruntime_reconciler.go    # AgentRuntime-specific reconciliation\n│   ├── codeinterpreter_reconciler.go # CodeInterpreter-specific reconciliation\n│   └── controller_test.go      # Controller tests\n├── informer/\n│   ├── factory.go              # Shared informer factory setup\n│   └── handlers.go             # Custom event handlers\n├── reconciler/\n│   ├── types.go                # Reconciler data structures\n│   ├── status.go               # Status update utilities\n│   ├── conditions.go           # Condition helpers\n│   └── finalizer.go            # Finalizer management\n├── client.go                   # Kubernetes client initialization (existing)\n├── service.go                  # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n├── server.go                   # HTTP server (existing)\n└── types.go                    # Request/Response types (existing)\n```\n\n### 1.3 Architecture Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Kubernetes API Server                           │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │ AgentRuntime    │  │ CodeInterpreter │  │ Pods/Service/ConfigMap  │ │\n│  │ (CRD)           │  │ (CRD)           │  │ (Managed Resources)     │ │\n│  └────────┬────────┘  └────────┬────────┘  └───────────┬────────────┘ │\n│           │                     │                        │              │\n└───────────┼─────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼──────────────┘\n            │                     │                        │\n            ▼                     ▼                        ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    K8s Reconciler Controller                            │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                    SharedInformerFactory                           │ │\n│  │  ┌──────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │ AgentRuntime Informer│    │ CodeInterpreter Informer        │ │ │\n│  │  └──────────┬───────────┘    └───────────────┬──────────────────┘ │ │\n│  │             │                                  │                    │ │\n│  │             ▼                                  ▼                    │ │\n│  │  ┌──────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │ AgentRuntime Lister  │    │ CodeInterpreter Lister           │ │ │\n│  │  └──────────────────────┘    └──────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│                                    │                                      │\n│                                    ▼                                      │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │              Reconciliation Loop (WorkQueue)                       │ │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │  Enqueue    │→ │   Reconcile  │→ │   Update    │→ │  Update  │ │ │\n│  │  │  (trigger)  │  │   (compare)  │  │   (diff)    │  │  Status  │ │ │\n│  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────┘ │ │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                    │\n                                    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     WorkloadManager Service                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │  HTTP API Layer (server.go)                                        │ │\n│  │  - CRUD operations for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter                │ │\n│  │  - Sandbox lifecycle management                                    │ │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.4 Reconciliation Flow\n\n```\n                    ┌─────────────────────┐\n                    │  Object Created/    │\n                    │  Updated/Deleted    │\n                    └──────────┬──────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────┐\n                    │  Informer Event     │\n                    │  (Add/Update/Delete)│\n                    └──────────┬──────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────┐\n                    │  Enqueue with Key   │\n                    │  (namespace/name)   │\n                    └──────────┬──────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────┐\n                    │  Get from Lister   │\n                    │  (cached object)    │\n                    └──────────┬──────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────┐\n                    │  Reconcile Object   │\n                    │                     │\n                    │  1. Fetch latest    │\n                    │  2. Check deletion  │\n                    │  3. Ensure finalizer│\n                    │  4. Reconcile spec  │\n                    │  5. Update status   │\n                    └──────────┬──────────┘\n                               │\n                               ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────┐\n                    │  Update Status     │\n                    │  (conditions, gen)  │\n                    └─────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Controller Types\n\n```go\n// ControllerConfig holds controller configuration\ntype ControllerConfig struct {\n    // Namespace to watch. Empty means all namespaces.\n    Namespace string\n    \n    // ResyncPeriod is the period to force a full sync\n    ResyncPeriod time.Duration\n    \n    // MaxConcurrentReconciles is the max concurrent reconciliation threads\n    MaxConcurrentReconciles int\n    \n    // Reconciler is the actual reconcile logic implementation\n    Reconciler Reconciler\n    \n    // Client is the Kubernetes clientset\n    Client kubernetes.Interface\n    \n    // Scheme is the API scheme\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n}\n\n// Controller manages the reconciliation loop\ntype Controller interface {\n    // Run starts the controller\n    Run(ctx context.Context, workers int) error\n    \n    // WaitForCacheSync waits for informers to sync\n    WaitForCacheSync(ctx context.Context) bool\n    \n    // GetHandler returns the event handler\n    GetHandler() cache.HandlerFuncs\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Reconciler Interface\n\n```go\n// Reconciler reconciles AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\ntype Reconciler interface {\n    // ReconcileAgentRuntime reconciles an AgentRuntime resource\n    ReconcileAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n    \n    // ReconcileCodeInterpreter reconciles a CodeInterpreter resource  \n    ReconcileCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n    \n    // SetupWithManager sets up the controller with a manager\n    SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager, options ControllerOptions) error\n}\n\n// AgentRuntimeReconciler reconciles AgentRuntime resources\ntype AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n    client     client.Client\n    scheme     *runtime.Scheme\n    log        logr.Logger\n    recorder   record.EventRecorder\n}\n\n// CodeInterpreterReconciler reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\ntype CodeInterpreterReconciler struct {\n    client     client.Client\n    scheme     *runtime.Scheme\n    log        logr.Logger\n    recorder   record.EventRecorder\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3 Reconciliation Request\n\n```go\n// Request contains the information required to reconcile a resource\ntype Request struct {\n    // Namespace is the namespace of the resource\n    Namespace string\n    \n    // Name is the name of the resource\n    Name string\n}\n```\n\n### 2.4 Reconciliation Result\n\n```go\n// Result contains the result of a reconciliation\ntype Result struct {\n    // Requeue requests immediate requeue\n    Requeue bool\n    \n    // RequeueAfter requests requeue after the specified duration\n    RequeueAfter time.Duration\n    \n    // Error is the reconciliation error\n    Error error\n}\n\n// RequeueOnError returns a Result that requeues on error\nfunc RequeueOnError(err error) Result {\n    return Result{Requeue: true, Error: err}\n}\n\n// NoRequeue returns a Result that does not requeue\nfunc NoRequeue() Result {\n    return Result{Requeue: false}\n}\n\n// RequeueAfter returns a Result that requeues after the specified duration\nfunc RequeueAfter(after time.Duration) Result {\n    return Result{Requeue: true, RequeueAfter: after}\n}\n```\n\n### 2.5 Status Types\n\n```go\n// ReconcileStatus contains the reconciliation status information\ntype ReconcileStatus struct {\n    // ObservedGeneration is the generation observed\n    ObservedGeneration int64\n    \n    // Conditions is the list of conditions\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition\n    \n    // Phase is the current phase\n    Phase ReconcilePhase\n    \n    // Message is the status message\n    Message string\n}\n\ntype ReconcilePhase string\n\nconst (\n    ReconcilePhasePending   ReconcilePhase = \"Pending\"\n    ReconcilePhaseRunning   ReconcilePhase = \"Running\"\n    ReconcilePhaseSucceeded ReconcilePhase = \"Succeeded\"\n    ReconcilePhaseFailed    ReconcilePhase = \"Failed\"\n)\n\n// Condition types for AgentRuntime\nconst (\n    AgentRuntimeConditionReady     = \"Ready\"\n    AgentRuntimeConditionReconciled = \"Reconciled\"\n    AgentRuntimeConditionInitialized = \"Initialized\"\n)\n\n// Condition types for CodeInterpreter\nconst (\n    CodeInterpreterConditionReady     = \"Ready\"\n    CodeInterpreterConditionReconciled = \"Reconciled\"\n    CodeInterpreterConditionPodReady   = \"PodReady\"\n    CodeInterpreterConditionWarmPoolReady = \"WarmPoolReady\"\n)\n```\n\n### 2.6 Finalizer Types\n\n```go\nconst (\n    // FinalizerAgentRuntime is the standard finalizer for AgentRuntime\n    FinalizerAgentRuntime = \"agentruntime.agentcube.volcano.sh/deletion-protection\"\n    \n    // FinalizerCodeInterpreter is the standard finalizer for CodeInterpreter\n    FinalizerCodeInterpreter = \"codeinterpreter.agentcube.volcano.sh/deletion-protection\"\n)\n\n// FinalizerManager handles finalizer operations\ntype FinalizerManager interface {\n    // AddFinalizer adds a finalizer to the resource\n    AddFinalizer(ctx context.Context, obj client.Object) error\n    \n    // RemoveFinalizer removes a finalizer from the resource\n    RemoveFinalizer(ctx context.Context, obj client.Object) error\n    \n    // HasFinalizer checks if the resource has a specific finalizer\n    HasFinalizer(obj client.Object, finalizer string) bool\n    \n    // EnsureFinalizer ensures the finalizer is present\n    EnsureFinalizer(ctx context.Context, obj client.Object, finalizer string) error\n}\n```\n\n### 2.7 Reconcile Options\n\n```go\n// ReconcileOptions contains options for reconciliation\ntype ReconcileOptions struct {\n    // SkipStatusUpdate skips updating the status\n    SkipStatusUpdate bool\n    \n    // SkipFinalizerCheck skips checking finalizers\n    SkipFinalizerCheck bool\n    \n    // ForceReconcile forces reconciliation even if up-to-date\n    ForceReconcile bool\n}\n\n// ReconcileOptionsFunc modifies ReconcileOptions\ntype ReconcileOptionsFunc func(*ReconcileOptions)\n\n// WithSkipStatusUpdate sets the skip status update option\nfunc WithSkipStatusUpdate(skip bool) ReconcileOptionsFunc {\n    return func(o *ReconcileOptions) {\n        o.SkipStatusUpdate = skip\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Controller Setup\n\nThe controller uses the controller-runtime framework for integration with Kubernetes:\n\n```go\n// NewAgentRuntimeReconciler creates a new AgentRuntimeReconciler\nfunc NewAgentRuntimeReconciler(\n    client client.Client,\n    log logr.Logger,\n    recorder record.EventRecorder,\n) *AgentRuntimeReconciler\n\n// NewCodeInterpreterReconciler creates a new CodeInterpreterReconciler\nfunc NewCodeInterpreterReconciler(\n    client client.Client,\n    log logr.Logger,\n    recorder record.EventRecorder,\n) *CodeInterpreterReconciler\n\n// SetupWithManager sets up the reconciler with the manager\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager, opts controller.Options) error {\n    return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n        For(&agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n        Owns(&corev1.Pod{}).\n        WithOptions(opts).\n        Complete(r)\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Reconciliation Triggers\n\n| Trigger | Source | Action |\n|---------|--------|--------|\n| Object Created | Informer (Add) | Enqueue Request |\n| Object Updated | Informer (Update) | Enqueue Request if spec/status changed |\n| Object Deleted | Informer (Delete) | Enqueue Request (cleanup) |\n| Owner Deleted | Owner's Informer | Enqueue dependent (cleanup) |\n| Periodic Sync | Controller (Resync) | Enqueue all objects |\n| Manual Retry | External | Enqueue specific Request |\n\n### 3.3 Status Update Contracts\n\n```go\n// UpdateStatus updates the resource status with reconciliation results\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) UpdateStatus(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    obj *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime,\n    conditions []metav1.Condition,\n    phase ReconcilePhase,\n) error {\n    obj.Status.ObservedGeneration = obj.Generation\n    obj.Status.Conditions = conditions\n    \n    // Set phase condition\n    metav1.SetStatusCondition(&obj.Status.Conditions, metav1.Condition{\n        Type:               string(phase),\n        Status:             metav1.ConditionTrue,\n        ObservedGeneration: obj.Generation,\n        LastTransitionTime: metav1.Now(),\n    })\n    \n    return r.client.Status().Update(ctx, obj)\n}\n\n// PatchStatus patches the resource status using strategic merge\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) PatchStatus(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    obj *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime,\n    patch *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime,\n) error {\n    return r.client.Status().Patch(ctx, patch, client.MergeFrom(obj))\n}\n```\n\n### 3.4 Event Recording\n\n```go\n// Events recorded during reconciliation\nconst (\n    // AgentRuntime Events\n    EventReconciling    = \"Reconciling\"\n    EventReconcileSucceeded = \"ReconcileSucceeded\"\n    EventReconcileFailed = \"ReconcileFailed\"\n    EventFinalizerAdded = \"FinalizerAdded\"\n    EventFinalizerRemoved = \"FinalizerRemoved\"\n    EventPodCreated = \"PodCreated\"\n    EventPodDeleted = \"PodDeleted\"\n    \n    // CodeInterpreter Events\n    EventWarmPoolCreating = \"WarmPoolCreating\"\n    EventWarmPoolReady = \"WarmPoolReady\"\n    EventPodReady = \"PodReady\"\n)\n\n// Example event recording\nr.recorder.Eventf(ar, corev1.EventTypeNormal, EventReconciling, \n    \"Reconciling AgentRuntime %s/%s\", ar.Namespace, ar.Name)\n```\n\n### 3.5 Owner Reference\n\nResources are owned by the CR and get garbage collected when CR is deleted:\n\n```go\n// OwnerReference creates an owner reference for the resource\nfunc OwnerReference(owner client.Object) []metav1.OwnerReference {\n    return []metav1.OwnerReference{\n        *metav1.NewControllerRef(owner, owner.GetObjectKind().GroupVersionKind()),\n    }\n}\n\n// IsOwnedBy checks if the object is owned by the given owner\nfunc IsOwnedBy(obj metav1.Object, owner metav1.OwnerReference) bool {\n    return obj.GetController() != nil && \n           *obj.GetController().UID == owner.UID\n}\n```\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    // ErrNotFound is returned when the resource is not found\n    ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"resource not found\")\n    \n    // ErrNotReady is returned when the resource is not ready\n    ErrNotReady = errors.New(\"resource not ready\")\n    \n    // ErrStaleGeneration is returned when the generation has changed\n    ErrStaleGeneration = errors.New(\"stale generation\")\n    \n    // ErrReconcileFailed is returned when reconciliation fails\n    ErrReconcileFailed = errors.New(\"reconciliation failed\")\n    \n    // ErrFinalizerFailed is returned when a finalizer operation fails\n    ErrFinalizerFailed = errors.New(\"finalizer operation failed\")\n    \n    // ErrDependencyNotReady is returned when a dependency is not ready\n    ErrDependencyNotReady = errors.New(\"dependency not ready\")\n    \n    // ErrMaxRetriesExceeded is returned when max retries are exceeded\n    ErrMaxRetriesExceeded = errors.New(\"max retries exceeded\")\n)\n```\n\n### 4.2 Error Handling Strategies\n\n```go\n// HandleError handles reconciliation errors with logging and status update\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) HandleError(ctx context.Context, ar *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, err error) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n    // Log the error\n    r.log.Error(err, \"Reconciliation failed\", \"namespace\", ar.Namespace, \"name\", ar.Name)\n    \n    // Record failure event\n    r.recorder.Eventf(ar, corev1.EventTypeWarning, EventReconcileFailed, \n        \"Reconciliation failed: %v\", err)\n    \n    // Update status with error condition\n    metav1.SetStatusCondition(&ar.Status.Conditions, metav1.Condition{\n        Type:    AgentRuntimeConditionReconciled,\n        Status:  metav1.ConditionFalse,\n        Reason:  \"ReconciliationFailed\",\n        Message: err.Error(),\n    })\n    \n    // Update status\n    if updateErr := r.client.Status().Update(ctx, ar); updateErr != nil {\n        r.log.Error(updateErr, \"Failed to update status\")\n    }\n    \n    // Determine requeue behavior\n    if errors.Is(err, ErrMaxRetriesExceeded) {\n        return reconcile.Result{}, nil // Don't requeue\n    }\n    \n    // Requeue after error with exponential backoff\n    return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Minute}, nil\n}\n\n// IsRetryable checks if an error is retryable\nfunc IsRetryable(err error) bool {\n    if errors.Is(err, context.DeadlineExceeded) {\n        return true\n    }\n    if errors.Is(err, ErrDependencyNotReady) {\n        return true\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 Error Response Mapping\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | K8s Reason | Action |\n|------------|-------------|------------|--------|\n| NotFound | 404 | NotFound | Stop reconciliation |\n| NotReady | Unprocessable | NotReady | Requeue |\n| StaleGeneration | Conflict | Conflict | Requeue with latest |\n| ReconcileFailed | 500 | InternalError | Requeue with backoff |\n| FinalizerFailed | 500 | InternalError | Requeue |\n| DependencyNotReady | Unprocessable | ErrDepNotReady | Requeue |\n| MaxRetriesExceeded | 500 | InternalError | Stop, alert |\n\n### 4.4 Condition Error Helpers\n\n```go\n// SetErrorCondition sets an error condition on the resource\nfunc SetErrorCondition(conditions *[]metav1.Condition, conditionType string, err error) {\n    metav1.SetStatusCondition(conditions, metav1.Condition{\n        Type:    conditionType,\n        Status:  metav1.ConditionFalse,\n        Reason:  \"Error\",\n        Message: err.Error(),\n    })\n}\n\n// SetSuccessCondition sets a success condition on the resource\nfunc SetSuccessCondition(conditions *[]metav1.Condition, conditionType string, message string) {\n    metav1.SetStatusCondition(conditions, metav1.Condition{\n        Type:               conditionType,\n        Status:             metav1.ConditionTrue,\n        Reason:             \"Success\",\n        Message:            message,\n        LastTransitionTime: metav1.Now(),\n    })\n}\n\n// SetPendingCondition sets a pending condition on the resource\nfunc SetPendingCondition(conditions *[]metav1.Condition, conditionType string, message string) {\n    metav1.SetStatusCondition(conditions, metav1.Condition{\n        Type:    conditionType,\n        Status:  metav1.ConditionUnknown,\n        Reason:  \"Pending\",\n        Message: message,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Tests\n\n#### Reconciler Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup fake client\n    fakeClient := fake.NewClientBuilder().\n        WithScheme(scheme).\n        WithObjects(agentRuntime).\n        Build()\n    \n    // Create reconciler\n    r := &AgentRuntimeReconciler{\n        client:   fakeClient,\n        log:      ctrl.Log.WithName(\"test\"),\n        recorder: record.NewFakeRecorder(10),\n    }\n    \n    // Test reconciliation\n    result, err := r.ReconcileAgentRuntime(ctx, reconcile.Request{\n        NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n            Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n        },\n    })\n    \n    // Assertions\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n    \n    // Verify finalizer was added\n    updatedAR := &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n    err = fakeClient.Get(ctx, key, updatedAR)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Contains(t, updatedAR.Finalizers, FinalizerAgentRuntime)\n}\n```\n\n#### Finalizer Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestFinalizerManager(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name       string\n        obj        client.Object\n        finalizer  string\n        wantHas    bool\n        wantUpdate bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name:       \"add finalizer to object without finalizer\",\n            obj:        &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{},\n            finalizer:  FinalizerAgentRuntime,\n            wantHas:    true,\n            wantUpdate: true,\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"object already has finalizer\",\n            obj: &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n                ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n                    Finalizers: []string{FinalizerAgentRuntime},\n                },\n            },\n            finalizer:  FinalizerAgentRuntime,\n            wantHas:    true,\n            wantUpdate: false,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            fm := NewFinalizerManager(fakeClient)\n            \n            has := fm.HasFinalizer(tt.obj, tt.finalizer)\n            assert.Equal(t, tt.wantHas, has)\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 5.2 Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Integration(t *testing.T) {\n    // Skip if not in integration test mode\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"Skipping integration tests\")\n    }\n    \n    // Use envtest (kubebuilder)\n    env, err := envtest.Environment()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Start test environment\n    cfg, err := env.Start()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    defer env.Stop()\n    \n    // Create manager\n    mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(cfg, ctrl.Options{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Register reconciler\n    err = (&AgentRuntimeReconciler{\n        Client:   mgr.GetClient(),\n        Log:      mgr.GetLogger(),\n        Recorder: mgr.GetEventRecorderFor(\"agentruntime-controller\"),\n    }).SetupWithManager(mgr, controller.Options{})\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Start manager in goroutine\n    go func() {\n        err := mgr.Start(ctx)\n        require.NoError(t, err)\n    }()\n    \n    // Wait for cache sync\n    require.True(t, mgr.GetCache().WaitForCacheSync(ctx))\n    \n    // Create test resource\n    ar := &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n        },\n        Spec: agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n            SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n            Ports:              []agentcubev1alpha1.TargetPort{{Port: 8080}},\n        },\n    }\n    \n    err = mgr.GetClient().Create(ctx, ar)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Wait for reconciliation\n    time.Sleep(2 * time.Second)\n    \n    // Verify status was updated\n    updatedAR := &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n    err = mgr.GetClient().Get(ctx, key, updatedAR)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Verify conditions\n    assert.Equal(t, 1, len(updatedAR.Status.Conditions))\n}\n```\n\n### 5.3 Controller Behavior Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected Output |\n|-----------|-------|-----------------|\n| Create Object | New AgentRuntime | Finalizer added, Status.Initialized = True |\n| Update Spec | Changed MaxSessionDuration | Status.Reconciled updated |\n| Update Status | Changed conditions | No requeue |\n| Delete with Finalizer | DeletionTimestamp set | Finalizer removed, then deleted |\n| Delete without Finalizer | DeletionTimestamp set | Directly deleted |\n| Dep Not Ready | Pod not created | Requeue |\n| Error During Reconcile | Reconciliation fails | Condition set to False, event recorded |\n\n### 5.4 Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Component | Target Coverage |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| controller.go | 80% |\n| reconciler.go | 85% |\n| agentruntime_reconciler.go | 85% |\n| codeinterpreter_reconciler.go | 85% |\n| status.go | 90% |\n| finalizer.go | 90% |\n| conditions.go | 90% |\n\n### 5.5 Fake Clients Usage\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client/fake\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n    agentcubev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n)\n\nfunc TestWithFakeClient(t *testing.T) {\n    // Initialize scheme with all types\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    agentcubev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n    corev1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n    \n    // Build fake client with initial objects\n    fakeClient := fake.NewClientBuilder().\n        WithScheme(scheme).\n        WithObjects(\n            &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n                ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n                    Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n                    Namespace: \"default\",\n                },\n            },\n        ).\n        WithStatusSubresource(\n            &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{},\n        ).\n        Build()\n    \n    // Use in reconciler\n    r := &AgentRuntimeReconciler{\n        client: fakeClient,\n    }\n    \n    // Test reconciliation\n    result, err := r.Reconcile(ctx, req)\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n}\n```\n\n## 6. Dependencies\n\n### 6.1 Required Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime | ^0.20.0 | Controller framework |\n| k8s.io/client-go | ^0.34.0 | Kubernetes client |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery | ^0.34.0 | API types |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | ^2.0 | Logging |\n| github.com/go-logr/logr | ^1.0 | Structured logging |\n| github.com/onsi/ginkgo | ^2.0 | Testing framework |\n| github.com/onsi/gomega | ^1.27 | Testing matchers |\n\n### 6.2 Internal Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | CRD types |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/listers | Listers for caching |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/informers | Informers for watching |\n\n## 7. Configuration\n\n### 7.1 Controller Configuration\n\n```go\n// ControllerOptions contains options for the controller\ntype ControllerOptions struct {\n    // MaxConcurrentReconciles is the number of concurrent reconciliation workers\n    MaxConcurrentReconciles int\n    \n    // ReconcilePeriod is the period between full reconciles\n    ReconcilePeriod time.Duration\n    \n    // FailureThreshold is the number of failures before stopping reconciliation\n    FailureThreshold int\n    \n    // ResourceNotFoundCacheDuration is the cache duration for not found errors\n    ResourceNotFoundCacheDuration time.Duration\n}\n\n// DefaultControllerOptions returns default options\nfunc DefaultControllerOptions() ControllerOptions {\n    return ControllerOptions{\n        MaxConcurrentReconciles:        10,\n        ReconcilePeriod:                time.Hour,\n        FailureThreshold:               3,\n        ResourceNotFoundCacheDuration: 1 * time.Minute,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 7.2 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| WORKLOAD_CONTROLLER_NAME | agentcube-workload-controller | Controller name for identity |\n| WORKLOAD_CONTROLLER_NAMESPACE | agentcube-system | Namespace to watch |\n| MAX_CONCURRENT_RECONCILES | 10 | Concurrent workers |\n| RECONCILE_PERIOD | 1h | Full sync period |\n| LOG_LEVEL | info | Logging level |\n\n### 7.3 Leader Election\n\nThe controller supports leader election for high availability:\n\n```go\n// LeaderElectionConfig for controller manager\nLeaderElection:           true,\nLeaderElectionID:         \"agentcube-workload-controller-lock\",\nLeaderElectionNamespace:  \"agentcube-system\",  // or operator namespace\n```\n\n## 8. Monitoring\n\n### 8.1 Metrics\n\n| Metric | Type | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| reconcile_total | Counter | Total reconciliation attempts |\n| reconcile_duration_seconds | Histogram | Reconciliation duration |\n| reconcile_errors_total | Counter | Reconciliation errors |\n| reconcile_retries_total | Counter | Retry count |\n| controller_queue_depth | Gauge | Work queue depth |\n| controller_worker_count | Gauge | Active worker count |\n\n### 8.2 Health Checks\n\n```go\n// Healthz endpoint returns controller health\nr.GET(\"/healthz\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n    // Check if informers are synced\n    if !controller.WaitForCacheSync(ctx) {\n        c.JSON(http.StatusServiceUnavailable, gin.H{\"status\": \"not ready\"})\n        return\n    }\n    c.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"status\": \"ready\"})\n})\n```\n\n## 9. Security\n\n### 9.1 RBAC Requirements\n\n```yaml\nrules:\n# AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRUD\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# Status subresource\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n\n# Managed resources (Pods, Services, ConfigMaps)\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\", \"secrets\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n\n# Events\n- apiGroups: [\"events.k8s.io\"]\n  resources: [\"events\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n```\n\n### 9.2 Security Considerations\n\n- Controller runs with minimal required RBAC permissions\n- Finalizers prevent garbage collection of resources with active dependents\n- Status updates use optimistic concurrency to prevent race conditions\n- All client operations include context with timeout\n\n## 10. References\n\n- [client-go library](deployment/client-go.md)\n- [AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition](design.md)\n- [AR-003: Shared Types and Constants](design.md)\n- [AR-006: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management](pkg/workloadmanager/design.md)\n- [controller-runtime documentation](https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime)\n- [Kubernetes Controller Pattern](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n- [kubebuilder](https://book.kubebuilder.io/)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/service_test.go\">\nERROR [127:9] cannot use &testWorkloadManager{…} (value of type *testWorkloadManager) as WorkloadManager value in return statement: *testWorkloadManager does not implement WorkloadManager (missing method DeleteSandbox)\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/client/informers/externalversions/factory.go\">\nERROR [103:12] informer.Shutdown undefined (type \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache\".SharedIndexInformer has no field or method Shutdown)\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/client/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go\">\nERROR [4:2] \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\" imported an